# API Routes

The API follows a RESTful design pattern with the following route groups:

## Authentication Routes
- [src/routes/auth.js](mdc:src/routes/auth.js) - Admin authentication endpoints
- [src/controllers/authController.js](mdc:src/controllers/authController.js) - Authentication logic

## Admin Routes
- [src/routes/admin.js](mdc:src/routes/admin.js) - Admin dashboard endpoints
- [src/controllers/adminController.js](mdc:src/controllers/adminController.js) - Admin operations
- [src/middleware/authAdmin.js](mdc:src/middleware/authAdmin.js) - Admin authentication middleware

## User Routes
- [src/routes/user.js](mdc:src/routes/user.js) - Public user endpoints
- [src/controllers/userController.js](mdc:src/controllers/userController.js) - User operations

## Store Routes
- [src/routes/store.js](mdc:src/routes/store.js) - Theme store endpoints
- [src/controllers/themeController.js](mdc:src/controllers/themeController.js) - Theme operations

## Common Routes
- [src/routes/common.js](mdc:src/routes/common.js) - Utility endpoints
- [src/controllers/petImageController.js](mdc:src/controllers/petImageController.js) - Pet image handling
